This paper deals with physical layer security in millimeter wave communications, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper specifically focuses on the fluctuating two-ray fading model, which is a channel model used in wireless communications (cs.MM) and the analysis of the physical layer security metrics involves the use of mathematical expressions and numerical simulations (cs.SY).
